            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The intimation made to Cornelius is a vision in a waking condition, caused by God (during the hour of prayer, which was sacred to the centurion on account of his high respect for Judaism), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " a manifestation of God made so as to be clearly perceptible to the inner sense of the pious man, conveyed by the medium of a clear (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "φανερῶς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") angelic appearance in vision, which Cornelius himself, ",
